HEADWORD: ground cover
<hw>ground" cov`er</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>low-growing plants planted in deep shade or on a steep
slope where turf is difficult to grow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>small plants other than saplings growing on a forest
floor.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ground cover, undergrowth.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Groundedly</ent>⟦br⟧
